  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The artifacts that were created in the Planning phase are used as part of preparing the organizations to apply asset&#xD;
    management. In particular the following artifacts are used during the Enablement phase:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Reuse Assessment&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Reuse Strategy&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Reuse Adoption and Incentive Plan&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Resources and Training Plan&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Enabling the enterprise top-down is certainly one approach. In this approach the Asset Governance Board is created,&#xD;
    then the Asset Manufacturing Team(s), and then the Asset Usage Teams. However, in many cases the enterprise has been&#xD;
    practicing informal reuse activities, where developers and others have been reusing artifacts which other teams or&#xD;
    individuals have created.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In many cases the enterprise will be enabled more formally in parallel, iteratively. Many organizations need to have a&#xD;
    formal Asset Governance Board created.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
